405
00:40:44,186 --> 00:40:48,672
We just bought them all wellingtons.

406
00:40:48,693 --> 00:40:50,396
All these monks lined up with green wellingtons.

407
00:40:52,818 --> 00:40:59,288
So that's a sort of very sort of roundabout touching upon our practice.

408
00:41:00,188 --> 00:41:01,050
And to...

409
00:41:01,552 --> 00:41:04,376
try and see how it melds into our daily life.

410
00:41:05,197 --> 00:41:07,960
So the morning sit, the evening sit.

411
00:41:08,280 --> 00:41:10,563
The morning sit gets you into the right frame.

412
00:41:10,623 --> 00:41:15,067
It reminds you of that level of awareness you want to take with you during the day.

413
00:41:15,126 --> 00:41:17,869
And throughout the day these little stops.

414
00:41:19,811 --> 00:41:21,673
If you can extend it to five minutes.

415
00:41:21,693 --> 00:41:22,414
You just relax.

416
00:41:25,858 --> 00:41:26,920
And then in the evenings,

417
00:41:27,405 --> 00:41:31,951
Always best when you come back from work or sometime even before you eat.

418
00:41:32,210 --> 00:41:33,733
It's always better.

419
00:41:33,753 --> 00:41:37,036
Just to allow any residues of the day to come.

420
00:41:37,056 --> 00:41:39,900
Some little irritations, some anxieties.

421
00:41:40,099 --> 00:41:43,282
Just let them, you know, let them exhaust themselves.

422
00:41:43,302 --> 00:41:45,626
They've got a nice evening ahead of them.

423
00:41:45,646 --> 00:41:47,668
And of course, sleep.

424
00:41:47,869 --> 00:41:48,869
Sleep's so important.

425
00:41:48,889 --> 00:41:49,630
You know, good sleep.

426
00:41:52,873 --> 00:41:56,518
You know, the idea of a rushed life

427
00:41:57,054 --> 00:42:01,561
And then it's time for bed and you sort of fling yourself into the bed.

428
00:42:01,601 --> 00:42:08,233
You sort of try to go to sleep, pull the clothes over you.

429
00:42:08,512 --> 00:42:10,275
And it's so counterproductive.

430
00:42:10,677 --> 00:42:16,826
The whole idea is to wind down, give yourself a full half hour just to let the days sort of disappear.

431
00:42:17,427 --> 00:42:24,438
Some pleasant music, some meta-meditation, something that draws the mind to a quietness and stillness.

432
00:42:24,458 --> 00:42:24,918
And that's

433
00:42:25,269 --> 00:42:28,313
That's your mental state just beneath your sleep.

434
00:42:28,333 --> 00:42:30,275
That's your subliminal state.

435
00:42:30,295 --> 00:42:35,820
If you go to bed with a subliminal state of anxiety, it keeps popping up, doesn't it?

436
00:42:35,860 --> 00:42:36,442
You can't rest.

437
00:42:38,003 --> 00:42:53,639
So no matter how bad the world is, we can spend a little time just allowing the mind to rest, the heart to rest, and then you get good sleep.

438
00:42:56,641 --> 00:43:04,677
So if questions come up, you know, out of this, at the end of the day we can bring up whatever needs to be for discussion.

439
00:43:06,461 --> 00:43:09,628
So I can only hope my words have been of some assistance.

440
00:43:09,648 --> 00:43:17,264
May you be liberated by your constant endeavor of all suffering sooner rather than later.

